Abstract in English: A vessel with a mooring recess on the bottom of the hull moors to a submerged buoyant mooring element anchored to the ocean bottom by hoisting the mooring element from a stowed position at a depth of net neutral buoyancy of the mooring element and its anchoring system into contact w1t11 the mooring recess. The mooring operation is completed safely, quickly, and positively by rapidly withdrawing seawater into the hull through all opening in the mooring recess so as to reduce the hydrostatic pressure acting on the top of the mooring element as the element comes into contact with the hull of the vessel. n e pressure reduction is sufficient to shift the mooring element and its anchoring system from a net negative to a net positive buoyancy condition at the keel depth of the vessel. the seawater may be withdrawn by a high capacity pump that is either specifically installed for this purpose or is part of a bow thruster system of a type commonly found on large vessels.

utilizes an armature mast, an armature boom having a Vertically and horizontally rotatable arm terminating in a reinforcing rod (rebar) tying guide, and associated hardware. The tying guide is aligned with a piece of vertical rebar, and a separate piece of horizontal rebar is placed adjacent and generally perpendictllar to the vertical rebar for securing thereto. The tying guide is then moved to engage an adjacent piece of vertical rebar, and the horizontal piece is bent inward for securing thereto. As the armature boom is moved about the mast and progressively raised, further vertical and horizontal pieces of rebar can be brought into juxtaposition and secured, thus generating a non-planar grid of rebar and other desired rebar weaves crossing patterns. An impermeable layer is placed over the grid, and a hardening material is applied to form a rigid shell. Further outside and inside base layers may be applied, and further outside and inside surface layers may be applied .

The pH of the electrolyte is preferably at least 0.2 units, more preferably from 0.5 units to more thabn 1.0 units above the pH value at which passivity of the anode would occur. The electrolyte may be for example sodium hydroxide or potassium hydroxide but is preferably lithium hydroxide which also acts as an alkali-silica reaction inhibitor.

Title in English: BEST SERVER SELECTION IN LAYERED CELLULAR RADIO SYSTEM
Abstract in English: A multi- level layered cellular radio architecture serves mobile subscriber stations moving within the system. Best server selection is performed for the mobile stations by assigning within each cell a preference value to each other one of the cells with which is associated by proximity of service area. The strength of the radio signal received by the mobile from the serving cell as well as the radio channels of associated cells is measured. A decision as to the best serving cell for the mobile station is made based upon both the preference value of the associated cells and the signal strength of their respective radio channels.

Title in English: Template and Process for Drilling and Completing Multiple Wells
Abstract in English: A template and process for drilling and completing multiple wells in subterranean formation. A template having a plurality of axially extending, divergent bores therethough is secured to surface or intermediate casing and a like plurality of subterranean wells are drilled through the bores and into the subterranean formation. Each well is separately cased to the well head at surface and separate production tubing is inserted into each well. Thus, remedial operations can be carried out in one well or fluid injected into a subterranean formation via one well while fluid, such as hydrocarbons, are simultaneously produced from a subterranean formation via the other well(s).

Title in English: Lifting device in an Armored Vehicule
Abstract in English: The nvention relates to a lifting device in an armoured vehicule. The lifting device comprises a holder, which can be engaged with a body to be raised, particularly a shell. A driven lifting element is also provided, by means of which the holder can be raised and lowered. in order to be able to take up in simple, flexible manner the shells, the lifting element is a cable drivable by means of a winch, which is guided on a pivotable, multycomponent articulated arm and carries the holder at its lower end. Preferably the cable passes through the articulated arm and its free end extends substantially vertically downwards, the articulated arm being pivotable substantially in a horizontal plane.

Title in English: A Device for Separating Condensate With Separator Elements.
Abstract in English: A device (1) for separating fatty, moisture-laden or oily condensate from rooms (2), for instance canteens, may be an underceiling, a hood or a combination of both. The device has known separator elements (3) which are held in a detachable condition by a supporting structure (4) in order that they can be cleaned in dishwashers, for instance. These separator elements (3) have collecting elements or coulisses (5) for the condensate, inclined so as to conduct the condensate to a gully (6) At least one collecting vessel (7) or a chain of collecting vessels (7) is slidably and or removably located in this gully (6), so that the condensate supplied by the separator element (3)or its coulisses (5) reaches this collecting vessel (7). The permanently installed gully (6) is therefore protected from this condensate by the collecting vessel(s) (7). For emptying and cleaning the collecting vessels (7) they can be slid out of the gully (6). (Figure 2)

Abstract in English: Apparatus for steering a drill bit(15) at the end of a drill string(1) within a bore hole to selectively effect drilling along either a curved path or a substantially straight path comprises a first downhole motor assembly)9) coupled to the drill bit(15) and operable to rotate the drill bit to effect drilling, the assembly(9) being arranged to angularly tilt the rotational axis of the drill bit tor assembly(9) to the drill string(1) and operable to rotate the first motor assembly(9). In addition the apparatus includes a lock sub(16) which is selectively actuable to (i) effect rotation of the drill bit(15) by the first motor assembly(9) while the first motor assembly is maintained at a defined axial orientation so as to cause drilling of the borehole along a curved path in the direction of tilt of the drill bit, or (ii) effect rotation of the drill bit(15) by the first motor assembly(9) while the first motor assembly is rotated by the second motor assembly(8) so as to cause drilling of the borehole along a substantially straight path. Rotation of the drill string as a whole is not required to effect drilling in either mode.

Title in English: VESSEL WITH IMPROVED SOLID PARTICLE EXTRACTION
Abstract in English: The invention concerns a vessel in which a chemical reaction is carried out in the presence of a catalyst and which comprises a bed (4) of solid catalytic particles, delimited by at Least one wall (1, 10, 1 1) and a base (2), the base comprising at least one gravity extraction means (3) for the particles and a succession of ridges and hollows forming pleats, the ridges and hollows being orientated towards the extraction means. The invention has particular application to mobile bed reactors, in particular those used for catalytic reforming of petroleum cuts .

Title in English: DISTRIBUTION DEVICE FOR THE TELECOMMUNICATION AND DATA TECHNIQUE
Abstract in English: The present invention relates to a distribution block for the telecommunication and data technique, in particular for the main distribution frame of telephone and data lines, comprising insulation displacement contact elements for the connection of the subscriber cables as well as of the exchange office cables, one-piece contact springs disposed in the interior of the modular-design distribution block, amounting bracket, in particular for receiving distribution blocks comprising a U-shaped tub, a device for guiding cables being rotatably moved in a partial section, and with cable guide portions. Mounting bracket 25 comprises in tub bottom 40 contact lugs 39 for the establishment of an electrically conducting and of a mechanical connection and openings 40 for the insertion of protection plugs or the like. The device for guiding cables comprises at a rack frame 48 or the like rigidly disposed cable guide portions 49 that are positioned upwardly and downwardly offset to cable guide portions 47.

Title in English: Technique for Replacement of Cryogenic/Cold Insulation on Equipment, Tanks, Piping, Valves, Flanges, Pipe Supports, Contraction Joints, Instruments, Fittings and similar objects under operational conditions.
Abstract in English: Technique for Replacement of Cryogenic / Cold Insulation System on equipment, tanks, piping, valves, flanges, pipe supports, contraction joints, instruments, fittings, etc. under operational conditions with cold / cryogenic temperatures down to minus 1800 celsius. After mechanically removing old insulation, ice, rust, scale, adhesive remains etc. from equipment/pipe surface, one coat of water dispersant antifreeze agent to be spayed into the equipment/pipe surface. One layer of rigid foam section shall be fitted with water dispersant petroleum jelly evenly applied on its inner surface used as joint sealer and adhesive. One layer of plastic foil to be fitted onto the surface used as joint sealer and adhesive. One layer of plastic foil to be fitted onto the surface working as sliding coat and secondary vapour barrier. Second or subsequent layers shall be applied as Decoupled Heat Insulation where a oversized metal reinforced plastic foil (primary vapour barrier) is loosely placed on supporting structure of rigid foam with longitudinal standing seams seal welded to building a cavity. Prefabricated protective metal casing to be fitted onto the vapour barrier foil. Spumous expandable polyurethane foam to be injected filling the compartments between sliding coat, supporting structure and primary vapour barrier foil/metal jacketing.

Title in English: HIGH FIDELITY VIBRATORY SOURCE SEISMIC METHOD USING A PLURALITY OF VIBRATOR SOURCES
Abstract in English: A method for recording and pre-processing high fidelity vibratory seismic data includes the steps of measuring the motion of the vibrator which is related to the vibrator applied force times a transfer function of minimum phase, causal, linear system relating the actual vibrator output with the measured vibrator motion, separation of signals according to generating source, determining a ratio by dividing the vibratory seismic data by the measured motion of the vibrator to remove the unknown applied force leaving the earth reflectivity times a time derivative divided by a minimum phase function, minimum phase band pass filtering the resulting ratio and performing minimum phase deconvolution to remove the time derivative divided by the transfer function of minimum phase. The method may also include shot ensemble deconvolution, receiver ensemble deconvolution, statics correction, F-K filtering for noise, zero phase spiking deconvolution and model dephasing. A signal directly proportional to the actual signal that the vibrator is sending into the ground is used in pre-processing. The vibrator motion is measured to provide a signal that is used to process the data. The data is divided by the relative of the actual transmitted signal in frequency domain

Title in English: HYDROPONIC CULTURE PROCEDURE AND DEVICE FOR IMPLEMENTING IT
Abstract in English: On parallel filiform supports (2) successively hanged channel units are established. The upper sheet (1) is fitted with holes (6) for the implantation of respective plants; the lower sheet (3), devoid of holes, acts as a sump; the intermediate sheets (4) are fitted with the same number of holes as the upper sheet (1), although longitudinally offset. The channel units are fed by a tube (8) that supplies the water and nutrients, which also provides a temperature control. From this tube emerges, above the upper sheet, a micro-tube or similar device for feeding the water individually. The liquid descends in the form of a cascade along the channel units and through the holes (7, 7') down to the lower channel unit (3), and in turn directs the plant roots along the same path of the nutrients.

A switch status sensor (1) is provided for counting on/off events of a switch (3) of a water meter (5). When an on/off event is detected my microcontroller (11), the microcontroller (11) supplies a "signature" signal, which is distinguiashable from electromagnetic moise to the switch (3). If this "signature" signal is detected as having passed through the switch (3) by the microcontroller (11), then it can be confirmed that the switch (3) is closed. Alternatively, if the "signature'" signal is not detected as having passed through the switch (3) by the microcontroller (11), then it is verified that switch (3) is open. Thus, the switch status sensor (1) can distinguish between false switch events caused by electromagnetic noice and true on/off events of the switch.

A switch status sensor (1) is provided for counting on/off events of a switch (3) of a water meter (5). When an on/off event is detected my microcontroller (11), the microcontroller (11) supplies a "signature" signal, which is distinguiashable from electromagnetic moise to the switch (3). If this "signature" signal is detected as having passed through the switch (3) by the microcontroller (11), then it can be confirmed that the switch (3) is closed. Alternatively, if the "signature'" signal is not detected as having passed through the switch (3) by the microcontroller (11), then it is verified that switch (3) is open. Thus, the switch status sensor (1) can distinguish between false switch events caused by electromagnetic noice and true on/off events of the switch.

Title in English: Process for the production of pipeline parts from plastic and pipeline part produced by this process
Abstract in English: Plastic pipes based on unsaturated polyester resins have low molecular weight polyester units with free hydroxyl groups. These functional groups present in particular in the resin-rich inner layer part forming the inner wall of the pipe are chemical reaction centres which react with a very wide range of compounds, such as, for example, water, inorganic and organic acids and oxidizing agents. Thus, when the polyester pipes are used in drinking water pipelines, the components dissolved out of the polyester resin by the chemical reaction of the water and the free hydroxyl groups may have an adverse effect on the quality of the drinking water. The invention relates to a process for the production of pipeline parts from polyester resin, which in turn have increased water resistance. The process according to the invention is distinguished by the fact that at least the polyester layer forming the inner surface of the pipe is treated with a medium containing at least one isocyanate. This treatment does in fact result in the formation of a matrix having polyurethane groups, which in turn impart to the plastics pipe not only the desired water resistance but also increased strength and impact strength.

Abstract in English: An automatic shutter for ventilating fans is disclosed. The shutter has an openable plate, two magnets and a balance weight. The openable plate is hinged to the outlet of the fan by two hinge shafts, of which the position leans to the upper portion of the plate. The two magnets cooperate with wind pressure acting on the plate, thus allowing the plate to be selectively closed or opened in accordance with the operation of the fan. The balance weight is mounted to the upper portion of the plate, thus rendering the lower portion of the plate slightly heavier than the upper portion. In an embodiment, two permanent magnets, having opposite magnetic poles, are respectively mounted to the outlet of the fan and the openable plate at corresponding positions. In another embodiment, an electric magnet, in place of a permanent magnet, is interiorly mounted to the outlet of the fan and is operated in conjunctIon with the fan, thus selectively and momentarily generating a magnetic force having the same magnetic pole as that of the permanent magnet of the openable plate when the fan is turned on.

Title in English: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR CORRECTING EFFECTS OF SHIP MOTION IN MARINE SEISMOLOGY MEASUREMENTS
Abstract in English: An apparatus and method for removing the distortion in marine seismic data resulting from the motion of the ship. The ship trails one or more seismic sources and receivers and moves forward at a known velocity. The seismic sources emit seismic waves that travel through the water and reflect off interfaces between rock formations below the ocean floor. The motion of the sources and receivers introduces distortion in the recorded seismic data that can be modeled using Doppler theory The data preferably is corrected for source motion independently from the correction for receiver motion. The seismic data is first corrected for receiver motion and then for source motion. The technique for correcting for source motion includes correlating the receiver-corrected data with a reference sweep signal, performing an F-K transform, performing an inverse F-K transform on a selected subset of the F-K transformed data, and computing appropriate correction filters for the data resulting from the inverse F-K transform. This process is repeated for all subsets of F-K transformed data and the resulting filtered data are summed together.

Abstract in English: A method and apparatus for mixing a first material and a second material is described in which the first material comprises a mixture of two or more dissimilar components which it is desired to separate. The method and apparatus involve forming an intimate mixture of the two materials prior to separating the two dissimilar components of the first material. The apparatus involves the use of a hydrocyclone for aerating or gasifying a feed stream, such as waste water containing oleophilic residue or food residue, to entrain the particles of residue within the air or gas bubbles prior to separating the oil or food residues from the carrier material, typically water. Instead of using the hydrocyclone as a separator, it is used as a mixer which provides surprising results and facilitates separation of the aerated components.

Title in English: Encapsulation of of Hazardous Waste Materials
Abstract in English: A method of encapsulating hazardous waste materials including heavy metals such as arsenic, mercury, nickel and chromium residues, as well as radioactive materials. The method involves adding the hazardous waste material to a settable composition, forming a slurry, and allowing the slurry to set to encapsulate the waste material. The settable composition is a powdered flowable cement composition containing calcium carbonate and a caustic magnesium oxide. Tests conducted on the encapsulated material indicate that virtually none of the hazardous waste material is leached out of the set composition which has a concrete-like appearance.

Abstract in English: In twin roll casting of steel strip, molten steel is introduced into the nip 16B between parallel casting rolls (16) to create casting pool (30) supported on casting surfaces (16A) of the rolls and the rolls are rotated to deliver solidified strip (20) downwardly from the nip. Casting surfaces (16A) are textured by a random pattern of discrete projections having pointed peaks and the strip is moved away from the casting pool at a speed of more than 60 meters per minute. In order to suppress chatter defects, the molten steel has a manganese content of less than 0.6% by weight and a silicon content in the range of 0.1 to 0.35% by weight. The random texture may be produced by grit blasting the casting surfaces on a substrate covered by a protective coating. Alternatively the texture may be produced by chemical deposition or electrodeposition of a coating onto a substrate to form the casting surfaces.

The second step is to sew the first layer of cover on the body of the frame by specialized sewing machines for this purpose and it is best to be between stitches and another half a centimeter distance and the number of sewing lines four or five lines around the perimeter of the frame body. The third step is to add the final layer of cover that will cover the first layer completely, making the final result as if we sew the garment from the inside with a magic depth so that the threads do not appear on the surface of the garment but are far in the depth of the garment.

Title in English: ARMOR PROTECTION OF LIGHTLY-ARMORED MILITARY FACILITIES
Abstract in English: The invention relates to the field of armor protection and may be used for protection of lightly-armored objects of armored-tank facilities against cumulative anti-tank grenades. The object is to increase the probability of destruction of cumulative grenades on a shield without the formation of a cumulative jet or to reduce the effective length of acumulative jet without the formation of breaks, cracks, dents on the main armor. The armor protection consists of main armor and a lattice shield fixed in front thereof at a distance, the lattice shield being made in the form of hinge-interconnected semi-shields of horizontally positioned metal plates, connected to each other by vertical rods. Additional protection shields of armored steel or glass cloth-base laminate are positioned between the main armor and the lattice shield. 2 dependent claims, 2 drawings.

Title in English: SYSTEM FOR THE CONTACTLESS RECOGNITION OF HAND AND FINGER LINES
Abstract in English: A process for reproducing hand and/or finger lines with a camera works without skin contact with the recording device. By using linearly or circularly polarized light in the paths of the illuminating and the reproducing light rays it is possible to obtain separate representations of the pattern of the epidermis and the one of the hypodermis. An image of the relief of the skin that is rich in contrast is obtained in this way, on the one hand, and it is possible to acquire information from the deeper disposed layers of the skin already supplied with blood. An algorithm searches the skin patterns of the palm of the hand for line elements of different strengths and directions (vectors). The computed numerical identification contains overall frequencies of vectors as well as amplitudes and phases of frequency components of projections of the vector images of both patterns. The process permits controlling people from a distance, complete protection of the measuring system and enhanced security against fraud

Title in English: SMART DOCUMENT SYSTEM WITH DOCUMENTS HAVING MAGNETIZED STRIPS AND /OR STORAGE CHIPS
Abstract in English: A system and method to produce and use new documents with magnetized strips and/or storage chips to avoid forging in the documents, the front faces of the documents carry imprinted visible data and a magnetic strip and/or storage chip containing stored encoded data, readable by a reader so it can be checked for conformity with the visible data to detect any unauthorized alterations to the documents. The present invention relates to a pen with a paper dispenser. The paper dispenser is composed of a reel tube having a lateral opening and a cavity, a central shaft disposed inside the cavity, a set of spring for shaft with one end inserted and fixed on the central shaft while the other end is connected with the beginning end of the reel for fixing it. The spring set for the shaft rotates in accordance with the central shaft and can release the paper through the lateral opening or furl the paper back to the cavity. An annular leafspring set for the paper roll is installed between the reel tube and the spring set for shaft. When the paper is released, of the spring set for shaft along radial direction pulls the paper roll out. On the other when the paper roll is curled back to the tube, the compressing force of the spring set for shaft along redial provides part of the cavity for receiving the paper.

Title in English: Turbine, Particularly Useful for small Aircraft
Abstract in English: A turbine essentially comprises a mechanical generating system including a combustion chamber (2) providing useful mechanical work on a high-speed shaft (8), a speed step-down system (22-23) for receiving rotational energy from the high-speed shaft and an output system including a low-speed shaft (24) receiving rotational energy from the speed step-down system for delivering mechanical from the turbine to a load. Auxiliary systems are kept to a minimum for lubrication, control, operation and start-up functions, thereby making the turbine particularly attractive for light aircraft. The combustion chamber is designed with deflectors (29) generating vortices in a secondary gas flow into the combustion chamber, thereby confining the flame front from penetrating into the cold region (3) of the chamber under variable operating conditions, simplifying cooling of the chamber walls. The highhspeed shaft is cantilever mounted on a pair of bearings (9A-9B) in the cold region and is provided with a longitudinal duct and an array of fine orifices (18) in the wall of the shaft which direct pressurized oil in the duct in the form of jets which impinge on the bearings with little relative speed, thereby increasing wetting of the bearing components. Oil is supplied to the duct by means of a positive-displacement pump (25) directly driven by the shaft. The output pressure of the pump provides a signal which is indicative of turbine speed and hence used to control the turbine start-up sequence. The turbine further includes devices for deecoupling vibrations between the three systems thereof, including a loosely mounted spline (16) coupling the high-speed shaft to the step-down system and disk dampening means (32) coupling the step-down system to the low-speed output shaft.

Title in English: A system and method for automated goods storage and retrieval
Abstract in English: A system and method for automated storage and retrieval that employs a two-dimensional, vertically oriented storage with storage areas arranged in a grid along a horizontal axis, a lift for access to one or more floors of the storage, and a vehicle transfer area for transfer of vehicles between an exterior transit way and the lift. Unique identification data is assigned to each vehicle upon access to the vehicle transfer area. Next, horological data is acquired corresponding to the identification data. Frequency data is calculated based on the identification data and the horological data, corresponding to the frequency of vehicle ingress and egress. The frequency data is stored in association with the identification data for later use. The vehicle is then transported to a storage area based on the frequency data, with vehicles having a higher frequency of ingress and egress stored in close proximity to the vehicle transfer area.

Title in English: METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR TRANSMISSION OF SEISMIC DATA
Abstract in English: The transmission method utilizes multiple seismic acquisition units (12) within an array (14) as intermediate short range radio receivers/transmitters to pass collected seismic data in relay fashion back to a control station (16). Any one seismic unit in the array is capable of transmitting radio signals to several other seismic units positioned within radio range of the transmitting unit, thus allowing the system to select an optimal transmission path. Utilizing an array of seismic units permits transmission routes back to a control station to be varied as needed. In transmissions from the most remote seismic unit to the control station, each unit within a string (18) receives seismic data from other unit sand transmits the received seismic data along with the receiving unit's locally stored seismic data. As transmission is passed along the chain, it is bounced between seismic units to be relayed by each unit in the array

Title in English: WHOLLY AUTOMATED MOBILE DEVICE AND CORRESPONDING FAST, ECONOMICAL AND COMPACT METHOD FOR PARKING PRIVATE VEHICLES
Abstract in English: The invention concerns an automated device for parking private vehicles, comprising a modular dismountable construction consisting of one or more automatic parking ramps whereon the driver leaves his/her vehicle, the vehicle being then positioned, mechanically centered, gripped and electronically measured, automatically, so that the vehicle can be displaced by computer and compactly stored. Said device consists essentially of a push system (tractor, 40) moving on a rail(tractorrail,42),gripping the vehicles at the wheels using forks with specific rollers (45),pulling same onto the lifting platform (31)in centered position on the rollers, moving the platform vertically, rotating the platform about its vertical axis and pushing the vehicle onto the parking platform (8).On request, the vehicles are once more pulled onto the lifting platform ,transported to the exit ramp and delivered to the user. The entire device consists of a reduced number of mobile components such that the construction and the use of said device are simple and economical. The inventive device uses the basic shapes of modern vehicles combined with the inventive method and a computerized allocation of places enables the space required as well as building and use costs to be considerably reduced compared to existing systems.

The invention also discloses a method of preparing a cable by extruding first layer of polymeric material upon at least one insulated conductor; serving a first layer of armor wires upon the polymeric material; softening the polymeric material to partially embed armor wires; extruding a second layer of polymeric material over the armor wires; serving a second layer outer armor wires thereupon; softening the polymeric material to partially embed the second armor wire layer; and optionally extruding a third layer of polymeric material over the outer armor wires embedded in the second layer of polymeric material. Further disclosed are methods of using the cables of the invention in seismic and wellbore operations, including logging operations.

Title in English: MULTI-CHAMBER HEAT ACCUMULATOR WHICH IS USED TO STORE THERMAL ENERGY AND TO PRODUCE ELECTRIC ENERGY
Abstract in English: The invention relates to a multi-chamber heat accumulator which is used to store thermal energy and to produce electric energy. Said multi-chamber heat accumulator has a trench-like structure which is introduced into the base, having a lower part, a, in particular, surrounding lateral wall and a cover. The trench-like structure has at least one inner area which is provided with a solid trench-like filling and at least one outer area with a second solid trench-like filling. The outer area at least partially surrounds the inner area. The trench-like filling of the inner area is separated, at least sectionally, from the trench-like filling of the outer area, by means of at least one separating wall. The inner area comprises at least one first pipe system which is provided with at least one inlet which is arranged in the inner area and at least one outlet emerging from the inner area which is used to guide the liquids through, which is arranged, at least sectionally, in the material of the first trench-like filling of the inner area. The invention also relates to a method for producing electric energy, comprising the following steps a) a multi-chamber heat accumulator is provided according to the inventive claims, b) energy is fed to the inner area via the first pipe system by guiding heated fluid such that the temperature of the inner area is on average at least 110° C, c) the thermal energy is fed and stored in the inner area in order to evaporate a work fluid, in particular, a mixture comprising ammonia and water, or to evaporate liquid, slightly volatile organic compounds or to evaporate liquefied inert gases, d) at least one steam turbine is driven by the steam emerging from the work fluid during the evaporation process and e) the kinetic energy is converted into electric energy by the moving steam turbine.

Title in English: A NOVEL APPROACH TO MODERATE WEATHER CONDITIONS BY EXPLOITING HEAT PIPE TECHNIQUE
Abstract in English: This work investigates a novel passive, environmentally friendly and very cost-effective technique to control/moderate the outdoor weather of hot climate regions that are nearby a large body of water. Large heat pipes (Fig.3) immersed into huge body of water are used to absorb heat from the surrounding a1r and release it into the water. The resulting temperature differences enhance the created pressure gradient between the land and water, which in turn accelerates the air movement (wind) from high to low pressure and therefore enhances the onshore breeze. Weather changes in a certain coastal area would have a positive reflection on its vicinity and to certain extent to the climate change and storm prevention. A certain number of large heat pipes can be immersed into water body. The evaporator section (1) is exposed to the surrounding ambient, while the condenser section (5) is immersed in the water. The evaporator section will be heated up by the effect of high surrounding temperature. This heat will be dissipated through the condenser section to the sea/river by the heat pipe process. As a result, the surrounding ambient temperature will be lessened and a higher pressure cooler air in the vicinity of the heat pips will be created. This high pressure air will strengthen the sea-breeze.

Title in English: EFFICIENT PROCESS FOR THE PREPARATION OF EPOXIDES BY ‎OXIDATION OF OLEFINES IN THE HOMOGENEOUS GAS PHASE
Abstract in English: The invention is directed to an economical one-step process for the ‎preparation of epoxides by oxidation of olefins in a homogeneous gas ‎phase reaction, wherein the olefine is reacted in a flow reactor with a gas ‎mixture of ozone and NO2 and/or NO as oxidants without use of a ‎catalyst, and whereby ozone and NO2 and/or NO are mixed in a mixing ‎chamber connected upstream to the flow reactor. The process is ‎characterized in that the olefine in the reaction zone of the flow reactor is ‎reacted at a reaction temperature of approximately 150°C to ‎approximately 450°C and a pressure of 250 mbar to 10 bar with the gas ‎mixture of the oxidant, whereby the carrier gas flow containing the ‎olefine is heated in a preheating zone of the flow reactor to a ‎temperature of 250°C to 650°C, and the gas mixture of the oxidant from ‎the mixing chamber, having ambient temperature, is turbulently mixed ‎with the olefine in the reaction zone of the flow reactor, so that the ‎reaction temperature is reached during the mixing and the ratio of ‎olefine-gas flow and gas flow of the oxidant is 5:1 to 1:1.‎

Abstract in English: A bore hole rotary reamer (1) includes a body (2) having cutters (4) contained in respective recesses (3) formed in the body (2). Each cutter (4) is rotatably mounted by one or more respective spindles (5). A bearing region (10) is formed by an inner bearing surface (11) rotatable on an outer surface of the spindle (5). At least one annular seal (12) about the spindle (5) prevents ingress of contaminant to the bearing region (10). A circumferential void (13) is formed between the inner bearing surface (11) and the outer bearing surface of the spindle (5) adjacent the seal (12). At least one passageway (17) extends in an axial direction of the spindle (5) to the circumferential void (13) and a piston (19) movable in the passageway (17) in response to supply of pressure to an outer side (19a) of the piston (19) from the environment which surrounds the reamer (1). The piston (19) transfers pressure to fluid in the cylindrical passage (17) on an inner side of the piston (19) to supply pressure to the circumferential void (13) and thereby to the seal (12) that is substantially determined by the pressure of the environment surrounding the reamer (1).

Title in English: Method for the enzymatic production of 2-hydroxy-2-methyl carboxylic acids
Abstract in English: The present invention relates to a method for the enzymatic production of 2-‎hydroxy-2-methyl carboxylic acids from 3-hydroxy carboxylic acids, where a 3-‎hydroxy carboxylic acid is produced in an aqueous reaction solution and/or is ‎added to this reaction solution and is incubated. The aqueous reaction solution ‎comprises a unit having 3-hydroxy-carboxylate-CoA mutase activity which has ‎both 3-hydroxy-carbonyl-CoA ester-producing and 3-hydroxy-carbonyl-CoA ester-‎isomerizing activity and converts the 3-hydroxy carboxylic acid into the ‎corresponding 2-hydroxy-2-methyl carboxylic acid which is isolated as acid or in ‎the form of its salts. In a preferred embodiment, the unit having 3-hydroxy-‎carboxylate-CoA mutase activity comprises an isolated cobalamin-dependent ‎mutase and where appropriate a 3-hydroxy-carbonyl-CoA ester-producing enzyme ‎or enzyme system or is a microorganism including them. The invention preferably ‎relates to a biotechnological process for producing 2-hydroxy-2-methyl carboxylic ‎acids, where microorganisms which have the desired mutase activity are cultured ‎in an aqueous system with the aid of simple natural products and intracellularly ‎formed 3-hydroxy-carbonyl-CoA esters are converted into the corresponding 2-‎hydroxy-2-methyl carboxylic acids. The invention likewise encompasses the ‎production of unsaturated 2-methyl carboxylic acids, where the 2-hydroxy-2-‎methyl carboxylic acids obtained are converted by dehydration into the ‎corresponding unsaturated 2-methyl carboxylic acids (methacrylic acid and ‎higher homologs).‎

Title in English: WATER BASED SMOKING PIPE HAVING ELECTRONIC IGNITION AND BURNING MEANS AND METHOD OF USE
Abstract in English: A traditional hubbly bubbly or hookah pipe having electronic burning capabilities and being able to run on battery power or electrical power is provided. The hubbly bubbly uses an electronic burning device that includes variable heat control and ceramic and glass burning devices. The battery power of such a device is provided by a lithium battery that, in one embodiment, provides an amount of burning time equal to the time of recharge. The device can be used in a vehicle or other mobile or remote areas due to the battery power and the more safe aspect of burning with electricity rather than open flame. The device provides variation on heating by either an analog twist switch or digital devices and software. The device of the present invention provides a mix of traditional water-based smoking pipe with modern and environmentally safer burning of inhalants.

Abstract in English: Composite Flat slab is a reinforced or a post tensioned concrete slab consisting of: • Precast Panel Layer: Concrete precast panels are placed at the bottom soffit of the slab supported by posts covering most of the plan layout . Its thickness ranges between 5 to 10 cm and it is reinforced with normal reinforcement. The width of these panels shall be normally about 1.20 meter or 2.4 meter. To obtain a monolithic slab, connection bars shall be provided to connect the precast panels with the cast-insitu concrete. These bars are used also for lifting and placing of the panels. (Figure -1). • Light Weight Material Blocks: Light weight blocks (like recycled polystyrene) are used to form voids inside the slab. The main purpose of providing these voids is to reduce the self weight of the slab. These blocks shall be placed over the precast panels evenly distributed with spacing in between forming one way or two way ribs. (Figures -2 & 3). • Reinforcement: Normal or post tension reinforcement shall be used in the ribs and over the slab-supporting elements. A top mesh of normal reinforcement shall be placed over the blocks. (Figures -2 & 3).

Title in English: Electrification of Buildings and Roads by Recycling Waste Wind Energy of Cooling Process of Condensing Units of HVAC System
Abstract in English: Power plant usually has an average efficiency of 34%, requiring about three units of fuel to produce one unit of power. Generally, residential, commercial and industrial building operations consume 76% of total electricity generation. This implies that a great attention should be given to the building sector if we are going to avoid hazardous climate change. Energy recycling is considered as one of the best solution in utilizing energy that would normally be wasted. It has been understand that much of the waste energy from manufacturing and power generation can be profitably recycled into useful heat and power, provided that the energy recycling facility is located at or near users. This novel idea represents the recycling solution in building-wise basis instead of centralized solution. The discharge air flow from the condensing unit/s of air-conditioning system and ventilation system can be directed through a ductwork to drive a vertical axis wind turbine/s. The amount of the generated power from the wind turbine will be able to electrify the whole premises and even the roads in the vicinity, with a very short payback period that would reach few days or even hours.

Title in English: A Novel Design of Cooling Tower with Superior Performance and independent ofgeographical location with Lower Initial & Operating Costs
Abstract in English: The size and cost of the cooling tower are increase with increasing heat load. The height of an evaporative cooling tower is usually limited by practical considerations such as structural strength, expense or architectural form. Wet bulb temperature is an important factor in performance of evaporative water cooling equipment, because it is the lowest temperature to which water can be cooled. This work investigates a new design of cooling tower, which independent of ambient condition or geographical location. The main principle is based on using one of the open-to-sky OTS shafts of multi-story building/s as a Body of the cooling tower and exploiting the exhausted cold foul air of the air-conditioned spaces as part of the induced draft air and as a condenser of the evaporation losses. To lessen/eliminate the high required demand power in pumping the hot water to higher elevation, an adequate vertical axis turbine is installed on the top of the cooling tower through ductwork as a source power. The proposed design concentrates on lowering the construction and operating costs, Lessening the makeup water and maximizing the heat load capacity, particularly in hot humid climate. Meanwhile, most of the limitations and constraints of the cooling towers have been overcome.

Title in English: Design of Rapidly Deployable Mast Mounting Assembly With GSM Antenna for the provision of Mobile Coverage for a moving Convoy using Satellite – BTS- to- BSC link.
Abstract in English: The Article provides the design of the Mounting technique required for fixing a rapidly deployable mast with GSM omni antenna on top of a vehicle. This is primarily required to provide mobile communication service to a moving convoy using Satellite –BTS-to –BSC link. To achieve this requirement a continuously moving GSM coverage pattern that follows the traveler is required. To implement the idea, a simple design is adopted to move the GSM Antenna and mast along with the traveler. The mounting is designed around a light weight Mast as a center pole supported with two tie rods. The tie rod position is predefined to keep the mast with antenna in an up right position with out swinging and swaying while on the move. The tie rod along with the mast is designed as a tripod which gives the required balance to the mast on top of the vehicle. The design is very simple so that the deployment and stowing of the mast needs no extra tools .The entire system can be folded back and stored on top of the vehicle with simple locking& un locking mechanism.

Title in English: The method of generating electricity power from hydraulic pressure
Abstract in English: To manufacture the system and assemble its components and to manufacture small electric generator. Motor that works with D.C current (Battery) to connected to a hydraulic pump and then connecting the pump with the hydraulic motor. With Iron pipes or with a high pressure hose. After that speed of the hydraulic motor that has centrifugal revolution (movement) will be reduced by a reduction gear box towards the generating head. After that the movement is transferred with a belt to the battery charger, to keep the battery in full charge. There is a filter between hydraulic oil tank and hydraulic pump. There is a hydraulic oil cooler (radiator) to cool hydraulic oil when it comes out from the motor before it goes to the tank. Title in English: Design and Implementation of Power Supply system for communication equipment in a vehicle providing mobile service coverage for a moving Convoy using Satellite –BTS- to- BSC link.
Abstract in English: The system meets the power requirement for providing Mobile Communication service to a moving convoy using Satellite –BTS to BSC link. The power supply is designed to meet the power requirement of 230 V AC and 24 V DC with high load requirement. Since the communication equipments are on the moving vehicle, external commercial power solution is not practical. Hence power supply is specially designed with out depending on the commercial source. 230 V AC power requirement for feeding the micro Base Transceiver Station (BTS) and Satellite Communication modem is generated by using the 12 V vehicle alternator in coordination with a set of inverters and battery banks. 24 V DC power is also required to operate Global positioning system, Antenna Control Unit and Radio frequency communication equipments. This is achieved by introducing an additional 24 V alternator in the vehicle which is coupled to the engine. The output voltage is converted to DC and smoothened using a set of battery banks. However, provision is also made to switch power source between internal or external while BTS is not in motion but with in the proximity of commercial power.

Title in English: PRODUCTION OF A NATURAL ANTIBIOTIC, AND ITS PROCESS DERIVED FROM DATE PITS DEGRADED BY FUNGI TO TREAT MICROBIAL BACTERIA OF BROILER CHICKENS
Abstract in English: The invention discloses a natural antibiotic product and the process for producing it from date pits degraded by fungi to treat microbial bacteria of broiler chickens. thereof, this invention documents a natural antibiotic in poultry feed and its process in using date pits degraded by fungus (Trichoderma reesei) to create a safer alternative for poultry. Degraded date pits by fungi can be produced using the Solid State Degradation system, inside an incubator. The effect of adding degraded date pits to the starter and finisher diets results in similar final body weights and feed conversion ratios in all treatments, indicating a possible replacement for part of the corn in broiler diets by date pits. The results of using date pits degraded by fungi as a natural antibiotic product in poultry feeds with a 5-10% concentration could reduce the microbial bacterial population (pathogenic diseases) such as: Salmonella spp, Campylobacter spp, Shigella spp and Escherichia coli, and could replace the currently used and recommended antibiotic as a chicken growth promoter and disease prevention and treatment for poultry.

Title in English: Glass Fiber Reinforced Plastic Pipes Encased in Reinforced Concrete
Abstract in English: Glass fiber reinforced plastic (GRP) pipes are widely used throughout the world for various applications. They can be manufactured in several ways and in accordance with different international specifications to suite each application. For underground pipe networks however, there are two methods of installation: a) Open-cut installation in which a trench is dug in the ground and the pipes laid out and connected together in the trench, and b) Micro tunneling in which the pipes are fed and continuously pushed (Jacked: hence called jacking pipes) behind a micro-tunneling/boring machine from one point to the other. Method a) is typically used for shallow networks in soft soil conditions while method b) is applicable to deep lines and in rock soils. The most widely used jacking pipes in the world are the reinforced concrete pipes (lined or unlined), other types of jacking pipes used are carbon steel and GRP pipes. For sewer lines in general however, it is important for the used pipe to have essential properties: 1) The inside surface of the pipe shall be smooth to facilitate the flow of sewer effluents, 2) the pipe shall be able to resist the chemically severe conditions resulting from the chemicals in the effluents, its temperature, and humidity, 3) Sufficiently strong to withstand the pressure forces resulting from the surrounding soil, and 4) economically competitive. Reinforced concrete only pipes can fulfill points (3) and (4) above, while GRP fulfills points (1) and (2). It is possible to manufacture GRP pipes that can fulfill points (1), (2), and (3) above and work as a jacking pipe, but then it will have to be too thick and therefore very expensive. Therefore, these new pipes (GRP pipes Encased in Reinforced Concrete) were invented to meet all the requirements of Jacking pipes).

Abstract in English: The value of Double Hanger comes from its ability to maintain the straightness of long, laundered clothes during the trip from the laundry to the house. In this context, long cloths could take many forms; like evening dresses, or traditional dresses of many parts of the world; like Arabian World, Japan, and some parts of Africa. For illustration purposes, the Arabian kandora will be used as a reference. Kandora is the name used in United Arab of Emirates for the Arabian dress of men. However, it is called differently from an Arabian country to another; like, Thoub in Saudi Arabia, Dishdasha in Kuwait, Gallibaya in Egypt, and Djellaba in Morocco. Although it has many names and few differences, the kandora is distinguished by its loose length that reaches ankles. Such length means that transporting it via private vehicle from the laundry to the house will often results in crumpling it. Usually, after laundering, the kandora gets hung by a regular hanger then put into a plastic bag. To be transformed via private vehicle, the hanger will be fixed to the grab handles in the backseats area. Where the upper half of Kandora will be hung, the lower part of the kandora will be left laying on the backseats. Because of the softness of the plastic bag and the movements of the vehicle, the lower half of the kandora often ends up fallen at the feet area and gets crumpled. As a solution, Double Hanger adds an extra hanging trait to the regular hanger and enables it to lift the whole kandora smoothly.

Title in English: Lever and Ball Electric Power Production Unit -LBEPPU
Abstract in English: The device consists of a shape which has motion and produces power. Shape: It consists of three cylinders connected to each other to form a semi triangle. Inside them are two magnetic balls of equal weight and size. Outside is a big unbalanced lever, interacts directly with the balls from one side, and indirectly with a small unbalanced lever from the other side. This small lever interacts with a freewheel and a chain connected to a big wheel. The tire of this wheel is attached to a dynamo connected to a battery to an electric lamp. Motion: The first ball is entered into the device to fall on one side of the big lever. When the second ball is entered, it forces the lever to push the first ball upwards to fall again on the previous side of the lever. The interaction and rotation begin upwards and downwards between the balls from one side, and the big lever from the other side. This makes the small lever move upwards and downwards, forcing the freewheel, chain, big wheel and the dynamo to spin. Power: When the dynamo spins, it produces electric power that transmits to a battery to illuminate the lamp.

Title in English: ENERGY FROM THE SEA (SEANERGY) ALTERNATIVE SUSTAINABLE ENERGY
Abstract in English: The sea is a tremendous source of energy waiting to be tapped. The huge mass of water constantly moving, surges with a vertical displacement of one to three meters in many parts of the world. My invention harnesses wave surges of the sea to lift the water by a unique reciprocating lift arrangement or rotary gear flywheel arrangement with turbine pumps through suitable pipes from the sea to a top reservoir on the platform and then fall down through guided pipes passing through turbine generators thus producing hydro-electricity (seanergy) and then drain back into the sea. Main benefits are: 1. Energy is sustainable. 2. A cheaper source of electricity. 3. Clean energy i.e. zero pollution. 4. Reversible opportunity for the polluted earth to rectify itself. 5. Humans are saved and earth is saved. 6. Risky nuclear power can be avoided. The invention is unique in the way of utilizing energy of the seas. Unlike oil platforms there are no gases and no fumes, no H2S, no fire hazards or no health hazards, quite operation, no separators or oil field related installations and equipments, minimum manpower requirement, less costly parts or items for maintenance and a host of several other advantages.

Title in English: HYDRAULIC TEST DEVICE FOR HEAD LOSS OF STRAINER AND TEST METHOD THEREOF
Abstract in English: Provided is a hydraulic test device for head loss of a strainer and a test method thereof. The hydraulic test device for head loss of a strainer includes a circulation pipe through which working fluid is circulated; an inflow container which temporarily stores the working fluid supplied through the circulation pipe; a container which receives and stores the working fluid through a straighter from the inflow container; a debris interceptor which is transversely disposed in the container so as to primarily filter debris injected through an injection part; sensors which sense a change in temperature and pressure of the working fluid in the container; a circulation pump which is disposed at one of branch pipes of the circulation pipe so as to circulate the working fluid; a flow meter which is disposed at the circulation pipe so as to measure a flow rate of the working fluid; a circulation heating heater which is disposed at the circulation pipe so as to heat the working fluid; and a data acquisition part which stores data sensed by each sensor, flow rate data measured by the flow meter and temperature data obtained by detecting heating temperature of the circulation heating heater

Title in English: LUGGAGE WITH A STRUCTURE TO ACCOMMODATE A COMPUTER
Abstract in English: A luggage with a structure to accommodate a computer is provided. The luggage includes a luggage body with a thermoplastic luggage cover. The luggage cover includes a secondary cover, a connection plate between the luggage cover and the secondary cover to enhance its strength, a zipper to close/open the secondary cover, and an inner bag disposed between the luggage cover and the secondary cover. The inner bag is composed of a limit wall and a bag plate made of a soft foam. The inner bag has a bag bottom which is not connected with the bottom of the luggage in a suspended state. The article in the inner bag can be fully protected by the thermoplastic luggage cover to accommodate and protect the computer therein. Between the inner bag, the secondary cover and the luggage cover is formed with two spaces to accommodate and separate articles.

Title in English: HYDRAULIC TEST DEVICE FOR HEAD LOSS OF STRAINER AND TEST METHOD THEREOF
Abstract in English: Provided is a hydraulic test device for head loss of a strainer and a test method thereof. The hydraulic test device for head loss of a strainer includes a circulation pipe through which working fluid is circulated; an inflow container which temporarily stores the working fluid supplied through the circulation pipe; a container which receives and stores the working fluid through a straighter from the inflow container; a debris interceptor which is transversely disposed in the container so as to primarily filter debris injected through an injection part; sensors which sense a change in temperature and pressure of the working fluid in the container; a circulation pump which is disposed at one of branch pipes of the circulation pipe so as to circulate the working fluid; a flow meter which is disposed at the circulation pipe so as to measure a flow rate of the working fluid; a circulation heating heater which is disposed at the circulation pipe so as to heat the working fluid; and a data acquisition part which stores data sensed by each sensor, flow rate data measured by the flow meter and temperature data obtained by detecting heating temperature of the circulation heating heater

Title in English: (electrap) red weevil trap through resonating chambers
Abstract in English: The red weevils (Rhynchophorus Ferrugineus) infestation is hitting the palm trees population in a very critical, severe way, creating many millions USD damages every year. All the previous devices and systems used till now to control the red weevils are generic and not directly targeting the specific pest. Based on resonant cavity principle, the system and method of the present invention overcome the problems of current pest control systems by adopting: • a proper radiation wave length, fitting to red weevils (RF) , by the means of appropriate sizes of and of proportions within the chamber, the aperture, and of the pheromone lure. • a trunked conical trap, casing the emission part, facilitating the entrance on and obstructing the exit from it by red weevils (RF) as well contributing to the best radiation emission. The radiating component is placed at a specific location of a truncated cone (the trap) with external side corrugated to facilitate the potential climbing in and the internal side fully flat to avoid the potential climbing out of the red weevils (RF).

Title in English: Shock Absorber Bumper For Recovery Trucks

Title in English: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR PROCESSING WASTE MATERIAL
Abstract in English: A system for ozone sterilization of waste material, includes a tank configured to receive waste material, ozonated water, and ozone gas. The system further includes a pump coupled to the tank to receive the waste material and the ozonated water from the tank and form a slurry. The pump includes a cutter assembly to reduce a particle size of the slurry through cutting. Additionally, the system includes a circulation loop coupled between the tank and the pump to receive the slurry from the pump and re-circulate the slurry to the tank until the slurry is sterilized. A method for ozone sterilization of waste material is also disclosed.

Obviously, we can modify and add any other surgical tools according to the specification needs and demands of different surgical teams. MAKTOUM SURGICAL ARM device can be made with a single, bifurcated or more extremities. Technically, novelty elements are in; “the single and double Air-Chamber existing inside the Base of The single and bifurcated Arm”, “the Special Claps existing on the Tool Holder for connection between the Arm and different tools” and “The Bifurcated Multi-Junctional Arm

Title in English: Nonintrusive inspection method and system of cargo type objects: vehicles, container trucks, train carriages
Abstract in English: The present invention consists of a method and a scanning system for the nonintrusive inspection of vehicles, container trucks and train carriages. The inspection can be realized without direct human intervention upon the inspected object, thus eliminating time wasting activities like physical control, unsealing, etc. The proposed method for nonintrusive inspection of vehicles and containers has a high inspection capacity (up to 200 vehicles per hour), by achieving a complete vehicle radiography (except the driver’s cabin), while driving through the scanning portal and building a system that implements this method, said system being geometrically optimized so that it can be transported rapidly in ISO standardized containers using conventional transport systems (airplane, ship, train, or terrestrial on public roads) in areas where a high level of security is mandatory. The system which implements the method presented earlier is constituted from a mobile scanning unit installed on a chassis 1, said chassis provided with a boom 3 that displays areas of detectors 10 specifically chosen according to the type of penetrant radiation used. In transport mode, the boom 3 is folded which assures the minimum gauge that would allow the compliance of the vehicle with the authorized dimensions of public road transport or in fitting the system into an ISO high cube standardized container. In scanning mode, the boom extends and takes an upside down “U” shape, sustaining at its inferior end, parallel with the detectors area 10 plan, the penetrant radiation source 9. The scanning system also includes a mobile control center which is positioned outside the exclusion area a and has the role to remotely command all the processes involved in the nonintrusive inspection. The mobile control center has an acquisition, processing, storage and image display subsystem 22. The scanning system includes a perimeter protection subsystem 32 and an automated traffic management subsystem 36.

Title in English: LIGHT WEIGHT CHOPPED WORN OUT TIRE'S CONCRETE BLOCKS
Abstract in English: It’s Light weight concrete blocks produced By a partial replacement of the mix’s aggregate volume (Sand and/or Gravel) with chopped worn out tires. Two of light weight mixes were produced : 1- Concrete mix with density of 1760 kg/m3, produced by replacement of 73% of gravel volume and 12% of sand volume with chopped worn out tires. 2- Mortar mix with density of 1694 kg/m3 , produced by replacement of 45% of sand volume with chopped worn out tires. Used Chopped worn out tires grading where between 0.30 mm minimum up to 6.35 mm maximum.As the density of traditional concrete is 2400 kg/m3 while the density of Chopped Worn out tires concrete is about 1760 kg/m3 to 1694 kg/m3 and the unit weight of the traditional blocks with the shape and dimension shown below, is about 23-24 kg. While the unit weight of the blocks produced, using chopped worn out tires is about 17-18 kg. For the same volume of traditional blocks, accordingly, it is specified as lightweight concrete masonry units. Lightweight Chopped Worn out Tire’s Concrete Blocks could be used to build the various walls in structural and nonstructural buildings. Production of Lightweight Chopped Worn out Tire’s Concrete Blocks will reduce the accumulation hazardous of worn-out tires wastage on the environment, and will change it to a useful material. Chopped Worn out Tire’s Concrete Blocks are lightweight, thermal insulation masonry units with low cost of production as they are produced from recycled wastages, While other traditional thermal insulation/light weight concrete masonry units are, produce using special technique or by adding chemicals, which are costly and have harmful effects on the environment.

Title in English: Patent Air & Oxygen Pumping System to Plants.
Abstract in English: In general, in the agricultural field when we water plants, oxygen is delivered to the plant from the atmosphere along with the water. However, most of the time this amount of oxygen is not sufficient enough to reach the plant’s roots in the deeper layers of the soil and as a consequence the plant lacks the sufficient amount of oxygen that’s necessary for its full development and growth. before planting the seeds, farmers plow the soil in order to turn over the upper and lower layer of the soil to bring up the nutrients to the upper surface as well as refresh the soil by bringing more oxygen to the surface. In our planet, there is 20% oxygen in the atmosphere. in forests or jungles there is 22% oxygen, while in the earth there is 5-7% oxygen. in this pioneering idea, sufficient and optimal amounts of air with oxygen will be supplied underneath the ground to the roots of the plants, vegetables, fruits, flowers, grass and/or trees.

Title in English: BIAXIALLY ORIENTED FOLD RETAINABLE POLYESTER FILM & A PROCESS FOR MANUFACTURING THEREOF
Abstract in English: The present invention relates to a biaxially oriented fold retainable polyester film and a process for manufacturing thereof. The biaxially oriented polyester film in the present invention is prepared by drawing a polyester sheet in both the machine direction (MD) as well as in transverse direction (TD). The fold retainable grade biaxially oriented polyester film of the said invention has haze levels in the range of 1% to 100%, in particularly between 1% to 95%. The film of the present invention has a bow angle (%) of not more than 3.28% at the centre of TD with a relaxation (%) given not exceeding 0.89 %, preferably between 0.56% to 0.89%. The poisson ratio of the said film is preferable between 0.7-0.93 and exhibits high deformability even at 10% elongation and above.

Title in English: METHOD FOR PROCESSING BAUXITE RESIDUE AND PRODUCTION OF GLASS ROCK MATERIAL
Abstract in English: A method is provided for processing bauxite residue. The method includes heating a bauxite residue charge mixture having a mass ratio of silicon dioxide to calcium oxide of about 0.5 to about 0.9 in a reducing atmosphere and melting the charge mixture at a temperature and at a pressure effective to form a metallic melt fraction and a slag melt fraction. The formed metallic melt fraction and the formed slag melt fraction may be separated and the slag melt fraction may be cooled and converted into a glass rock material.

Abstract in English: One-WayDatasystem (ODS) (herein called the system) is a system thathas beendesigned and developedbyDEWAstaffto meet thegrowing needto connect theOTnetworkswith internet-connectednetworksfor the purposes ofestablishing an integratedandcentralized informationsystems orfor the purposes ofcommunicationacross countrieswithOEMs for remote services. The system ensures unidirectional flow of data from OT networks to internet-connected networks and not vice versa, so as to secure OT networks against hacking through the internet. The system consists of a One-Way Data Diode (ODD) connected to two computers, one transmitter and one receiver by RJ45 cables using User Datagram Protocol (UDP). The ODD ensures physical isolationbetween the two networksin the reverse directionby taking advantage offiber-optictechnologyproperties using thein-housedeveloped software. The transmittercomputer fitches -from the OT network– the data orfiles that are required to besent via an interface computerand transmits them to the receiver computer through the ODD. Title in English: DESIGN SOLUTION FOR CRANK SHAFT WITH INTERMEDIAT LOAD BEARING
Abstract in English: This Invention is related to new design solution of crank shaft that is to isolate it from any wear or direct impact during engine running. Each journal of main bearing and big end bearing has 2 to 4 threaded holes or locks to secure additional intermediate load bearings; extra shaped high finished material made of same crank shaft material or other equivalent material with 2 to 4 holes that match to crank shaft threaded holes, to be fixed and fastened with countersunk (flat) socket screws on crankshaft journals of main bearings and big end bearings. These new intermediate load bearings (invention) are isolating crank shaft from direct surface contact with main bearings and big end bearings and are fastening on crank shaft journals with countersunk (flat) socket screws or hidden locks do not conflict with the crankshaft rotation. In case of wear of conventional main bearings and big end bearings, since the crank shaft is isolated with intermediate load bearings, then the repair requires only the replacement of intermediate load bearings of new design and conventional sets of main bearing and big end bearing together with the use of new countersunk (flat) socket screws. With the new design the wear is affecting on both intermediate load bearings and conventional sets of main bearing and big end bearing instead of crank shaft journals and they can be replaced in the same position Hence, neither engine nor crank shaft needs to remove for the purpose of under size cutting or replacement of the crank shaft. Connecting rod big end diameter and lower end of piston sleeve to be modified that to give the piston the freedom of movement to the end of strokes.

Title in English: Gravity Driven Generator for Sustainable Movement. (GDGSM)
Abstract in English: The innovation in this invention, is the method by which we use the force, created by the interaction of the gravitational field upon different elements (liquids, gases, solids), to produce electrical energy. Humanity has used the force of gravity for a long time in water and air driven turbines for electricity production. But in those technologies, the force used, is the one created by the gravitational field in the particular element, and once this element gives away its energy, it continues its movement and cannot be used in the same turbine again. In the gravity driven generator for sustainable movement (GDGSM), in order to create rotation force we use the fact that elements with different atomic weight, are subjected to different forces, while, exposed to gravity field. In the gravity driven generator for unsustainable movement (GDGSM) we use the difference in the force created between air (gas) and the liquid element to create a buoyant force, which through the solid element to be able to perform work. This is the main difference between the 2 types of technology as mentioned above. In conventional technology we have 1 element which gives its energy, and it the gravity driven generator for sustainable movement (GDGSM) we have 3 elements interacting, creating buoyant force which than perform work.

Title in English: Way to identify the fingerprints through DNA analysis
Abstract in English: The idea of the invention is of great value for forensic investigations. It will give a lead to the investigations where there is no clue about the suspect or the criminal(s) are unknown. The invented methodology will identify the genes responsible for the fingerprints patterns in humans and hence using these genes to give an indication about the fingerprints pattern using DNA evidence. DNA will be extracted form biological evidences found at crime scene, which then will be treated with specific reagents for PCR reactions including DNA primers and DNA polymerase. After that using up-to-date technology in reading the sequences of the DNA, genes will be analyzed in the recovered sample and pattern will be deducted according to the results. High number of genes is expected to be responsible for the fingerprints pattern in addition to the environmental effects, which affect the fingerprints pattern in the embryonic stage of the new born.

Title in English: UNIFIED MOBILE-BASED ADVERTISING SYSTEM AND METHOD
Abstract in English: A unified mobile-based advertising system is provided. The unified mobile-based advertising system includes a memory having computer-readable instructions stored therein and a processor. The processor is configured to receive a campaign request from an advertiser. The campaign request corresponds to a campaign associated with one or more products promoted by the advertiser. The processor is further configured to provide a selection of a plurality of mobile network communication channels to the advertiser. The plurality of mobile network communication channels are operated by one or more mobile network operators. In addition the processor is configured to receive a selection of one or more mobile network communication channels from the advertiser. The one or more mobile network communication channels are operated by a respective mobile network operator. The processor is also configured to determine, using a subscriber database, one or more subscribers of the mobile network operator targeted for the campaign. Moreover, the processor is configured to generate customized campaign content for the one or more subscribers and deliver the customized campaign content to the one or more subscribers using the selected one or more mobile network communication channels.

Abstract in English: This invention brought forward a new technology to make the shower system more connected to the smart home environment. The convention shower system has primarily one function related to supply water flow for while taking the shower. There are some technologies provides timer or sort of lights as an indicative of the shower time. However, this invented technology provides a much more sophisticated and interconnected device to achieve different objectives through several functionalities as illustrated below. - The device integrated with the smart home protocol - Has an interface with the smart phone application - Has an intelligent display outside the bath with new communication protocols - Linked with user profiles which would be used to measure the consumption for each individual - Enhance the awareness of each profile to change the consumption culture - Contains dashboard for high level consumption monitoring - Provides more safe architecture for the entire system using a wireless architecture with the overall system components - The sensors, pumps, PLCs, etc are all newly developed in an innovative system. As an alignment with the national and international strategies represented with the water distribution authorities’ visions and missions to provide a continuous saving consumption awareness for all types of water consumers. On the other hand, statically a 25% of the bath water consumption versus the total water consumption in each customer water supply invoice. This invention oriented to save/reduce the consumption of those 25% by inventing several techniques and functions. We invented an idea to save the un-suitable water because of undesired water temperature. Normally each person will waist the water before commencing the shower until the water temperature becomes to his body desired temperature, based on conducted study, varies from 5-7 liters per single shower use. The same concept covers also all types of sinks inside the bathrooms or kitchen. The invention outcomes showing that the total saving close to 15% of the total water consumption as an initial phase “Interconnected Shower system” which can be also implemented on all types of water supply inside and outside the buildings (Residential, commercial, governmental, industrials, public facilities etc..), which obviously would maximize the benefits and increases saving the overall water consumption.

Title in English: Intelligent Warning Tape and Intelligent column
Abstract in English: A system for determining the angular position of a synchronous motor includes an encoder with a friction wheel engaging a rotating surface of the motor. The friction wheel is spun by the rotation of the motor, and the encoder generates a signal corresponding to the angular position of the friction wheel An independent sensor is provided to generate a pulse once per revolution of the motor. The independent sensor detects the presence of a target on the rotating surface of the motor and generates the pulse when the target is proximate to the sensor. A controller receives the signal corresponding to the angular position of the friction wheel as well as the pulse generated by the independent sensor to determine the angular position of the motor. The controller compensates the angular position of the motor each time the pulse is generated, correcting accumulated position error.

Title in English: Smart Parking With Eco-Cooling System Using Solar Panel
Abstract in English: A foldable garage with eco-cooling system totally powered by solar energy is proposed. In this system, the driver would park the car. He/ She would switch on the system via remote control. A foldable garage would safely cover the car. When the temperature reaches a threshold (40ºC), the micro controller would process such input by turning on the air conditioner. The whole system is powered a rechargeable battery that is connected to the solar panels. Accordingly, the hot air will be released through the slots and the cold air will remain inside the garage. The cold fresh air that is released from the air conditioning will replace the hot air, and this cycle will go over and over again until the temperature inside the garage reaches (30ºC). There will be a safety sensor to ensure safe opening/closing of the garage.

Title in English: Efficiency enhancing apparatus and methods for a heat exchange system
Abstract in English: A method and apparatus for improving refrigeration and air conditioning efficiency for use with a heat exchange system having a compressor, condenser, evaporator, expansion valve, and circulating refrigerant. The apparatus includes a liquid refrigerant containing vessel having a refrigerant entrance and a refrigerant exit with the vessel positioned in the heat exchange system between the condenser and the evaporator, and means for creating a turbulent flow of liquefied refrigerant. The apparatus further preferably includes a refrigerant bypass path to sub-cool a portion of the refrigerant within the vessel; a disk positioned at the liquid refrigerant entrance to develop a low pressure area on the back side and create a turbulent flow of refrigerant entering the vessel; and a refrigerant valve incorporated into the refrigerant path downstream of the expansion valve and before the coil which develops a vortex that continues through the refrigerant coil.

Abstract in English: Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics (i.e., STEM) education has emerged as one of the most sought-after curriculum designs for integrating science, technology, engineering, and mathematics into curriculum. Our STEM EDU BOX is a class room and practical Lab area inside a combined shipping container. Our apparatus contains hydroponic and aquaponic units with dedicated Hi-tech class room, where students can explore there learning experience out of the class room. The seed deposition of seeds takes place in a rockwool bed in a prebuilt seed germination system containing 4 set trays within this STEM EDU BOX. The upper side of the tray is subjected to light of the proper frequencies to promote growth in plants. A nutrient solution is injected onto the trays and the developing root mass of the plants, while controlling temperature, humidity, and carbon dioxide within the STEM EDU BOX control room. Two weeks old plants are transplanted to NFts and other trays from germination system. The plants are harvested resulting from the seeds at a desired stage of growth. The Aquaponics system in the STEM EDU BOX is a working model of organic food production. Aquaponics combines fish and plant together.
