The practical model discloses a device of treating concrete wastewater by using carbon dioxide gas, including processing equipment. Primary sedimentation tank is set in one side of the processing equipment. Primary sedimentation tank is connected with carbon dioxide reaction tank through the inlet pipe. The improved water pump is set on the inlet pipe, and the end of the inlet pipe is set with drainage pipe. Fan is set at one side of the carbon dioxide reaction tank. One end of the fan is connected with the upper part of carbon dioxide reaction tank’s inner chamber by intake pipe, and on the other end of the fan with the lower part of carbon dioxide reaction tank’s inner chamber by exhaust pipe. The other end of the carbon dioxide reaction tank is set with inlet port, and the tank is connected to restoration sedimentation tank by drain pipe. The restoration sedimentation tank is connected with filter funnel by filtering tube. Quartz sand net is set inside the filter funnel, and with clear water tank is set at the bottom of the filter funnel. This practical model can reduce the original water’s TDS without using reverse osmosis equipment, and the equipment is simple, with cost low.

Title in English: Smart Management for Sustainable Excavation Outputs
Abstract in English: Dubai Municipality introduced a smart initiative to handle waste sand, which considered as a waste. The continuous need of land to be used as waste dump. Effect of CO2 produced from trucks while transferring the sand to the dump area located at outskirts of Dubai (about45KM from city center), the loss of the precious beach sand. The initiative is based on an innovative idea of converting sand waste to a valuable product,97%of the sand gets recycled. the service is called“sand transfer/supply request” which manages exchanging excavated sand. All applications for excess excavated sand or demand of backfill sand is handled by a GIS smart application to balance between demand and supply through the shortest distance possible. The initiative saved dump land at a cost of 3billion AED. Carbon foot print was reduced 82,000tons(equal to planting 1.5 million trees) due to distance traveled reduction. Preserving huge amount of beach sand and send it back to coastal areas. Sand fill is delivered to citizens houses & Government projects for free(approximate cost of237million AED), Project contributed to reduce the cost of sand from 22to10 AED/m3,Quality sand is sent to concrete factories to be reused or to fill the abandoned excavated construction sites.

Title in English: INTELLIGENT WITNESSES TO BE USED IN FORENSIC DNA TEST
Abstract in English: In DNA testing, witness step is very important during the DNA examination. It is essential to ensure that samples are transferred from one step to another without mixing in the samples. This process is performed by persons who are competent in the DNA fingerprint tests. Due to the great effort exerted by the witness during the DNA examination process, and the inability to benefit from this person for other tests, the idea of intelligent witness had been developed which summarized as synthesis of artificial DNA with known genetic information added to the samples from the stage of collection and transferred with the samples from one step to another during the examination and read as the normal DNA fingerprint read.

A soiling detection apparatus operable to detect a soiling level of a photovoltaic panel. The apparatus comprising a photovoltaic panel operable to generate an electrical output in response to light being incident on the panel and in dependence upon a soiling level of the photovoltaic panel. The apparatus comprises a pyranometer operable to generate an irradiance signal which relates to an irradiance level of light incident on the pyranometer. The pyranometer is positioned with respect to the photovoltaic panel such that the photovoltaic panel and the pyranometer can receive substantially the same solar radiation level as each other. The apparatus comprises calculating means operable to calculate a reference output value from the irradiance signal which relates to an ideal electrical output of the photovoltaic panel at a predetermined operating condition. The apparatus further comprises measuring means operable to measure the electrical output of the photovoltaic panel at the predetermined operating condition, and comparing means operable to compare the measured electrical output of the photovoltaic panel at the predetermined operating condition with the reference output value so as to generate a comparison value. The apparatus comprises outputting means operable to output a cleaning signal when the comparison value is greater than a cleaning threshold value.

Abstract in English: A ferrule replacement apparatus for replacing a ferrule of a pipe. The apparatus comprises an elongate ferrule holder comprising a shaft and a ferrule gripping portion arranged to be able to receive and grip the ferrule. The apparatus comprises a valve having an open position and a closed position. The valve comprises a bore through which the ferrule gripping portion can move when the valve is in the open position, and pipe engaging means arranged to be able to engage the pipe to form a fluid tight seal with the pipe when the apparatus is mounted on the pipe over the ferrule. The apparatus comprises a main body comprising a sliding seal arranged to cooperate with the shaft of the ferrule holder so that the ferrule holder can move axially with respect to the main body. The main body is arranged to be able to cooperate with the valve to form a fluid tight chamber between the main body and the valve. The ferrule holder is removeably connectable to the main body so as to be able to form a fluid tight connection between the ferrule holder and the main body when mounted to the main body. The ferrule gripping portion is moveable through the bore when the valve is in the open position between a first position where the shaft is within the bore and where the ferrule gripping portion can engage the ferrule when the apparatus is mounted on the pipe over the ferrule, and a second position where the ferrule gripping portion is within the chamber so that the valve can be in the closed position to fluidly isolate the chamber from the pipe engaging means and so that the ferrule holder can be detached from the main body. Title in English: Float valve comprising a trigger mechanism
Abstract in English: A float valve comprises a valve body having an internal bore and which comprises an inlet and an outlet. The inlet and the outlet are arranged so as to be able to be in fluid communication with each other via the internal bore. The valve comprises an elongate arm pivotably mounted to the valve body. The elongate arm comprises a float mounted on the elongate arm and moveable with respect to the valve body. The valve comprises a valve seat, and a piston moveable within the internal bore between an open position in which fluid can flow between the inlet and the outlet, and a closed position in which the piston can cooperate with the valve seat so as to prevent fluid flow between the inlet and the outlet. The valve further comprises a first resilient biasing element arranged so as to be able to urge the piston towards the valve seat, and a trigger mechanism arranged to be able to hold the piston in the open position. The trigger mechanism is arranged to be able to cooperate with the elongate arm so that, at a first threshold position of the float with respect to the valve body, the piston can be released from the open position and be urged by the first resilient biasing element to the closed position. The valve comprises a reset mechanism arranged to be able to cooperate with the elongate arm so as to be able to move the piston from the closed position to the open position where it is held by the trigger mechanism when the float moves from the first threshold position to a second threshold position with respect to the valve body.

Title in English: Composite Groynes - Timber logs fixed to steel tubular piles
Abstract in English: Groynes are structures perpendicular or almost perpendicular to the coastline. Groynes are widely used to protect the coastline against erosion caused by littoral drift. Traditionally, groynes are constructed using rocks, but other materials like timber, steel and concrete are also used. Compared to the rock groynes, the timber groynes are preferred due to its aesthetic and natural appearance, less footprint and thus less disturbance to the coastal processes and environment. However, till date the use of timber logs in groyne construction is limited to shallow depths due to the non-availability of longer lengths of logs with uniform cross-section. This led to the current concept of composite groynes, where the timber logs are fixed to continuously driven steel tubular piles. The timber logs are plugged through the fresh concrete, partially filled inside steel piles and the gap between the successive timber logs is filled with concrete to form an impermeable groyne. For aesthetic reasons, the top of steel piles has been fixed lower than the Lowest Astronomical Tide (LAT), in this case 0.5m below LAT, so that the steel piles are not visible at all tidal conditions. As the steel tubular piles can be fabricated to any desired length, the proposed composite groynes are applicable for any given water depth.

Title in English: SYSTEM, METHOD, AND COMPUTER PROGRAM PRODUCT FOR MULTI-LAYER ENCRYPTION OF AN EFFICIENT BROADCAST MESSAGE
Abstract in English: A system, method, and computer program product are provided for multi-layer encryption of an efficient broadcast message. In use, a message is identified that includes data to be broadcasted to a plurality of recipients as well as identifiers of the plurality of recipients. The message is encrypted using a first encryption process to form a first header portion and a first data portion. Additionally, the message with the first data portion is encrypted using a second encryption process to form a second header portion and a second data portion. Further, the first header portion is encrypted using a third encryption process to form a third header portion. A multi-layer efficient broadcast message is then formed for broadcasting the data to the plurality of recipients, the multi-layer efficient broadcast message including the second header portion, the third header portion, and the second data portion.

Title in English: Air condition Unit with self cooling unit
Abstract in English: This invention consists of completely new air conditioning unit, and it is completely different from the traditional air conditioning units which been used for many years and usually contains tow parts, an external part which placed outside the place to be cooled like street or outdoor playground, in this part there is Compressor and Condenser or Hot Coil and fan, this part is usually high source all traditional air conditioning units. The other part is internal and contains the evaporator, fan , and blower to push the cold air towards the cooling area. Through this new invention, we provide friendly environment air conditioning units that reduce the heat emission resulting from The outer section of the conventional air conditioning units, this is to reduce the greenhouse effect, which in turn has a positive reflection on the environment. The new air conditioning unit is considered as a single unit that is installed or fixed in the place where it is to be cooled. We have removed the outer section which is usually placed outside like the street or outside yard and this part usually has a high source of heat and we have merged it in the same internal unit by building a new body for the new unit, The first part of the air conditioner has a compressor, a fan and / or to cool the condenser or hot coil, the second or internal section of the air conditioner has an inflator or fan directed towards the evaporator to push the cold air towards the place where to be cooled. This is can be controlled by special control unit that has special keys or by remote control to increase or decrease the cooling degrees. Thus, the new air conditioning unit considered as one unit of the new air conditioner issued that has self-cooling mechanism to the hot air that generated by the hot coil which is located in the air conditioning unit, this happened by by passing the air as shown in Figure (7) so that the hot air gets out of the inflator to enter the tube inside the conditioning unit, and then enter it to the cooling unit to cool it in different ways as shown in the cases described in the general description, short description and protection elements. In this invention five methods have been used to cool the Condenser or Hot Coil and to cool its high heat, and reduce or prevent the heat as required to be acceptable. This is done by adding Heat Exchanger and Condenser as the new dryer machines mechanism. Or by immersing the Condenser or Hot Coil in a sealed box which has liquid, such as 3M Novec Engineering Fluid or any liquid that has the same function. The characteristics of this liquid enable to cool the high heat caused by electronics while running. Or we cool the Heat Exchanger and Condenser which exist in the dryer machine by making the parts that enter the Heat Exchanger and Condenser inside the liquid Novec Engineering Fluid to cool the parts that touch it from the exchanger and condenser and to cool the hot air coming from the Hot Coil. In this way we can reduce the heat that produced from the new air conditioning units emitted from the Hot Coil. Or we can cool the Heat Exchanger and Condenser in any way of cooling system, for example using Thermoelectric Peltier refrigeration Or we can put a small cooling unit, its function is to push the cold through the blower to the heat source on Condenser or Hot Coil Of the air conditioner that belongs to the air conditioning of the place to be cooled, and the body of the condenser and the composter that cools the Hot Coil is immersed in a container that contains the liquid Novec Engineering Fluid or any substance that has the same function of work.

Abstract in English: The present invention relates to a method for constructing a non-soil-displacement pile by soil gelling, in which a pile is installed in the soil gelled by mixing a gelling agent with the soil loosened by the rotational penetration of agitation equipment and thus placed in the bearing ground such that it is possible to prevent the generation of excavated soil during the construction of the pile, thereby minimizing the effect on the surrounding ground and simultaneously greatly shortening the pile construction period. The method for constructing a non-soil-displacement pile by soil gelling in order to install a pile (3) in the ground (1), according to the present invention, comprises: (a) the step of measuring a construction position for the pile (3); (b) the step of enabling rotational penetration of agitation equipment (6) into the construction position for the pile (3), spraying a gelling agent while loosening the soil of the ground (1) to the bearing ground, and mixing the loosened soil and the gelling agent, thereby gelling the soil; (c) the step of removing the agitation equipment (6) and installing the pile (3) in the gelled soil (5) by its own weight so as to secure the pile (3) on the bearing ground; and (d) the step of curing the gelled soil (5) so as to fix the pile (3).

Title in English: A MORTAR COOLING SYSTEM AND PROCESS
Abstract in English: There is provided a cooling system and process for cooling a barrel of a mortar system for increasing a firing frequency of the mortar system while the mortar system is in an operational mode. The cooling system and process of the present invention combines the air and water cooling to provide better cooling than the traditional implemented solutions. One of the functions of the cooling system and process of the present invention is to reduce or eliminate the increase in barrel temperature of the mortar system during firing, and to reduce the time required to reduce the barrel temperature of the mortar system following firing. The reduction of the increase in barrel temperature during firing increase the number of bombs that can be fired before the maximum temperature limit is reached. The increase cooling after firing reduces the time required to cool the barrel to allow further firings. The cooling system and process in accordance with the present invention allows to improve the cooling level of the barrel and the firing frequency of the mortar.

Title in English: EUSTACHIAN TUBE DYSFUNCTION ASSESSMENT METHOD AND APPARATUS
Abstract in English: A Eustachian tube dysfunction assessment system and method of assessing level of dysfunction is disclosed. The system is made up nasal pressure sensor (160), external ear canal sensor (170), probe assembly (105) connected to the palate of the patient, data acquisition block (140), computer (180) and software (190) controlling the whole system. Eustachian tube dysfunction level is assessed by applying stimulation pulses via probe assembly (105) to mTVP, mLVP muscles of the patient while monitoring output of the external ear canal sensor (170). By stimulating mTVP, mLVP muscles individually or together with different level stimulation level pulses, the level of Eustachian dysfunction is assessed.

Abstract in English: A manufacturing method of silica nanofluid comprising, (a) dispersing silica sol in deionized water; (b) introducing a silane coupling agent and performing a silane reaction to modify a surface of a silica nanoparticle; (c) filtering and dialyzing the silica nanoparticle in distilled water to recover the silica nanoparticle; and (d) dispersing the silica nanoparticle in brine, is provided. Title in English: Novel Selective medium for Gram negative bacteria.
Abstract in English: Bacterial species are broadly classified into two groups based upon their staining characteristics i.e. Gram positive organisms and Gram negative organisms. These classification is the first step in identification and characterization of bacterial species isolated from environment or from clinical samples. Although, many commercially available media are viable, there is a continuous effort to develop better selective media to bacteria that cannot be grown on existing media. While exploring antibacterial property of a plant products, we observed that it has the potential to selectively inhibit growth of certain types of bacteria. This lead us to do the experiments which resulted in developing this media which selectively allowed the growth of only Gram negative bacteria. Mueller Hinton Agar (MHA) was used as the base media and was modified to develop MHA-X (MHA containing the plant product, which we designate as plant-X). Water extract of 25 % (W / V) plant X material was used and added to the MHA to prepare the new media which was designated as MHA-X25. Number of strains of several medically important major Gram negative pathogens were tested; which included Escherichia coli, Klebsiella pneumoniae, Salmonella spp. and Pseudomonas aeruginosa and observed that all these bacterial species grew on MHA-X25. However, none of the major types of Gram positive pathogens such as Staphylococcus aureus, Streptococcus pneumoniae, Streptococcus pyogenes, Bacillus spp. and Enterococcus spp. grew on MHA-X25. Taken together, these findings show that MHA-X25 is a newly developed selective media for culture of Gram negative bacteria.

Title in English: Automatic Recognition of Plastic (3D-printed) threat in Baggage X-rays using Artificial Intelligence
Abstract in English: Full specification: In this page, the 3 novel innovations will be discussed in more details. 1- Innovation in creating a full 3D-printed threat x-ray image dataset: a. The innovation lies in the fact that data collection of plastic x-ray images was collected in a systematic and scientific way, not by randomly screening the baggage that contain the threat as it is in the scientific papers. This was as follows: i. Collecting x-ray images of the plastic threat being alone in the baggage without any other material so that the algorithm starts to learn the features of the gun without any noises from external objects. ii. Then collecting additional images of x-rays, but this time we add some organic materials in addition with the plastic threat (orange colors in x-ray) to mimic the colors of the plastic threat. This way the algorithm will start to note the difference in terms of shape too and it will no longer get fooled from the organic materials. iii. Finally, collection of baggage x-ray images that mimic that baggage of a normal passenger. That means the baggage must include both metallic and non-metallic materials, complex mixtures were made in addition to the plastic threat being hidden in the bag so that the algorithm generalize its knowledge to real life scenarios. 2- Innovation in Threat Image Projection technique: to create new synthetic images from original images that appear authentic to increase the dataset: a. There are other approaches for threat image projection, which is the projection of a threat from one image to another normal image to multiply the number of threat images, however some of these techniques are not very accurate. This means that new image will have cues that appear to be fake and that can be dangerous to the algorithm. b. The technique of (Solving Poisson equations with a predefined boundary condition) is an accurate technique as I have seen and makes the x-ray projection to be authentic. Again, this technique is used for other domains such as in nature, but I have tried it on x-ray threat images, and it worked greatly. 3- Innovation in the used of an already publicly available deep learning network by fine tuning its settings: a. A pretrained network was used (Googlenet) that is already available b. Speed and duration of learning the algorithm was adjusted to allow the network to learn the features of the hard to detect plastic threats (0.001 and 120 respectively) c. The augmentation settings of the algorithm are important to overcome overfitting however, the Scaling, zooming, and intensity augmentation of the images was disabled since it was experimented that is negatively affect the accuracy. Moreover, augmentations such as reflections and rotations were allowed in order to overcome overfitting problems. function protection in school buses to avoid forgetting children, The device is a buzzer that alerts and issues alarms The process of operation of this device in the case of the closure of the bus engine is running Motion Sensor system is the process of reading the movement in the case of extinguishing the engine and leave the driver without making sure the bus is free of children in any case in the event that the child Sleeping as soon as the movement of the child even a simple movement gives the device a loud alarm so that it draws the attention of any person near the bus while forgetting any child in the bus in addition to the process of communication and automatically the bus driver or the person in charge or the operating room and through this contact is to know the location of the bus via a Smart map..

Title in English: Gas Turbines Air Intake Cooling Systems Integrated Controller
Abstract in English: At peak ambient temperatures, Gas Turbine (GT) performance is reduced due to lower air density which leads to lower mass flow in the combustion turbine. Gas Turbines based in hot ambient regions use various technologies for Power augmentation of power plants. The optimal use of these power augmentation technologies helps raise Output and Efficiency with lower NOx emissions while minimizing resource input such as water use. Some GTs have several Coolers installed and operated simultaneously. These technologies are totally independent as they are manufactured and supplied / installed by different manufacturers and suppliers. Each of these technologies work best during a certain ambient condition at which time the other technology would not be able to achieve its optimum performance due to it particular design. This application for patent is for designing and producing a compatible integrated controller that will act as a common governing control system to detect the input parameters at any time and coordinate in between the different control systems of cooling systems that are installed in one GT to achieve optimized operation between the different cooling technologies.

Title in English: Granulated Date Kernel Herbal Tea with/without Natural Color with Complete, Transparent, and Easy Liquor Extraction
Abstract in English: Date kernel is one of the most valuable plant wastes in the food industry. Given its high nutritional value for humans, the need to design a mechanism for its introduction into the global food chain and its mass industrial production is strongly felt. Granulated date kernel herbal tea is a product that has managed to introduce a way to public use and mass production. This herbal tea is consumed like tea and only requires boiling water and 3-4 minutes of brewing. In this method, the hard and solid date kernel (roasted or not-roasted) is powdered to allow liquor extraction of all kernel particles in boiling water. However, transforming the kernel into powder is not sufficient to make it consumable. Due to the particles' dispersion and molecular weight, the powder stays afloat in water and its extracted liquor will contain solid particles, which accordingly causes non-transparency and poor quality of the extracted liquor. By adding a sedimentation (or translucent) agent to the kernel powder, the extracted liquor becomes clear and transparent. Shaping and granulizing of the powder will be possible by adding a natural binding agent. Moreover, with the addition of natural edible colors to this blend, a transparent extract of various colors could be obtained, though its original color may vary from light yellow to dark yellow. After mixing the above ingredients and converting the powder into paste by adding water, the processes of shaping and changing the paste into granular particles and drying are then executed. The dried product is ready to be brewed. Keywords: Palm Date Kernel, Date Seed, Date pit, Powder, Granule, Herbal Tea, Liquor, Extract

Title in English: A SYSTEM FOR MONITORING AND CONTROLLING A DYNAMIC NETWORK
Abstract in English: The invention relates to a system for monitoring and controlling a dynamic network such as an oil, gas, or water pipeline. The system includes a plurality of sensors for measuring aspects of a state of the network with each sensor being associated with a segment of the network and connected to a virtual sensor which accumulates and preprocesses measurements from the sensors for each segment of the network. Title in English: Solar water brine recycling and evaporation system for production of water, salts and minerals.
Abstract in English: Abstract Solar water brine recycling and evaporation system for production of water, salts and minerals. The system is based on parabolic-cylindrical reflectors (concentrators), and a closed evaporation pond with a cover to speed up the evaporation process. The pond is connected to condensation storage unit which also acts as a heat exchanger. The brine is heated to 120-125 ° C, at a pressure of 0.2-0.25 MPa and enters the evaporator of a special design, where evaporation occurs at atmospheric pressure and separation of the crystallized sediment occurs. The sediment is then divided into salt, minerals and metals. The parabolic evaporation system has individual protection of the reflective surface in the form of shockproof glass. The system recycles reject water (brine), produces clean water, salt, minerals and metals. It significantly reduces the installation cost and reduces maintenance costs. The system also takes less space than traditional evaporation systems.

ABSTRACT The aim of this project is to develop a smart Intensive Care Unit (ICU) mechanical ventilator which applies artificial intelligence principle to support COVID19 infected patients since it is mandatory to isolate them, while the doctor and caretaker can monitor remotely. The pressure in the air and oxygen supply line in the ICU is controlled to deliver an FiO2 mix from an air-oxygen blender to the patient during inhalations, and remains idle during exhalations. Exhaled gases are released by the patient himself limited by PEEP control valve and End Tidal CO2 sensor senses the CO2 in the exhaust. The blood oxygen saturation level of the patient is measured using an infrared pulse-oxygen probe, and FiO2 auto-regulator controller applies the 6th sense and changes the FiO2 level based on the oxygen saturation level. FiO2 auto-regulator has an oxygen and air blender to control the oxygen-air mix proportion. A pressure sensor and flow sensor are provided at the inlet airway to the patient and their signals trigger the pressure relief valve if limit is exceeded. In case of any AC power failure, the backup battery system will start functioning automatically with an alarm indication for power source change and battery charge level. Artificial Intelligence is used on a windows platform for Machine Learning to provide alerts and display the vital parameters of patients based on threshold values and recommend actions. The mobile application assists the doctors and care takers to monitor the patient remotely.

Abstract in English: Abstract A fuel catalyst apparatus for treating and improving combustion efficiency is provided that includes at least one hydride producing element, and at least one element of greater activity on the electrolytic scale than the hydride producing element and at least one element of lesser activity on the electrolytic scale than the hydride producing element. The metal alloy fuel catalyst relates in general to methods and devices for treating fuels prior to combustion to increase combustion efficiency and thereby reduce exhaust emissions. It has long been an objective of many individuals within different industries to develop devices and methods for improving the combustion efficiency of hydrocarbon fuel burning systems. A breakthrough in improving fuel efficiency is the development of a fuel catalyst that could be used to treat fuel prior to combustion. While the fuel catalyst has proven to be effective, the underlying mechanism of operation has not been previously understood. It is therefore an object of the present invention to determine the underlying mechanism of operation of the fuel catalyst so that additional catalysts can be analytically developed.

Abstract in English: A waterbody rejuvenation device (100) includes a flow inlet (102), a coarse sieve (104), a finer sieve (105), a pump (106), a submersible motor (108), a multi-phase multi-stage flow multiplier (MMFM) (110), floats (202a and 202b), a basket filter (115), an air/dosing intake (116) and an air/dosing valve (116A). The flow inlet (102) draws laden water with suspended organic and inorganic impurities including one or more of algae, floating debris, suspended solids, and settled sludge with petrified organic material, turbidity fine dust present in a water body. The coarse sieve (104) filters coarse dirt and debris from the received laden water. The finer sieve (105) further filters a portion of the laden water entering the pump (106), that has filtered through the coarse sieve (105). The pump (106) draws and pressurizes the laden water. The submersible motor (108) provides mechanical power to the pump (106). The MMFM (110) inducts and adds additional fluid flow at every stage of the laden water with suspended solids and gaseous fluids, thus increasing the total flow rate in addition to the pump flow rate that is handled for filtering or separating suspended solids and/or aerating the fluid passing through the MMFM (110). The floats (202a and 202b) facilitate the levels of the waterbody rejuvenation device (100). The basket filter (115) receives the fluid exiting from the MMFM (110) and collects and further filters the finer suspended solids in the fluid before returning into the water body. The air/dosing intake (116) and an air/dosing valve (116A) inducts one or more of air from the atmosphere and/ or ozone, Hydrogen Peroxide, Sodium Hypochlorite, and oxidizing agents, herbicides from the source connected to the air-dosing intake (116) by the MMFM (110).

Title in English: Smart Employee Card for Fever Detection and Social Destining
Abstract in English: The smart card is connected to the Internet through a development board that works with Internet of Things (IoT) (Figure 1 No. 9). The readings display in a mobile app in the smartphone or tablet (Figure 2). Smart card has a large photo of the user's face (Figure 1 No. 5) and employee’s details (Figure 1 No. 6). Smart Card has a thermal camera that measures person’s body temperature from a distance that reach up to two meters (Figure 1 No. 4). It gives a sound alarm (Figure 1 No. 8), red light alarm (Figure 1 No. 2) and vibration alarm (Figure 1 No. 10) when approaching a person with a high body temperature. It also alerts the user when the social distancing violation is detected by an ultrasonic distance sensor (Figure 1 No. 7). It begins with a vibration alert when the distance between the user and the other person becomes less than two meters (Figure 1 No. 10). It begins light alarm (Figure 1 No. 2), and sound alarm (Figure 1 No. 8) when distance becomes less than 1 meter. Smart Card works with a battery that is charged via a USB-C port (Figure 1 No. 11). The card contains NFC technology which enables the card holder to access the security gates (Figure 1 No. 12).

Title in English: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR EXTENDING SHELF-LIFE OF MEAT & POULTRY
Abstract in English: The current invention covers an improved meat-packaging procedure for packaging meat cuts for long-term storage at temperatures of between 28° and 42°F. The process includes sealing meat cuts or full poultry birds or bird pieces within a master bag containing (i) oxygen scavenger materials capable of reducing the residual oxygen content of the atmosphere within the bag to 0 ppm within 96 hours of sealing, and (ii) a CO2 generator capable to generate CO2. Gas is injected into the master bag to form a CO2-rich storage environment of at least 50% CO2. Depending upon the gas-volume and oxygen scavengers design in the master-bag to maintain diffusion, the CO2 generators may not be needed in the master-bag. For meat trays containing meat with poor color stability, oxygen scavengers are preferably placed within the meat trays. For cuts with good color stability, the oxygen scavengers may be placed outside the meat trays. Meat can be stored by this system for up to 10 weeks and up to twelve days of retail display life. Poultry can be stored for 28+ days by this system.

More particularly, the invention encompasses a below grade, blind side, waterproofing sheet membrane with adhesive, and having at least one layer of moderate reflectivity granular particle layer that are fully or partly embedded into the adhesive layer, and where the average reflectivity of the exposed granular particles is below 55 percent reflectivity on a standard reflectivity scale. The inventive waterproofing layer having the waterproofing sheet membrane, and an adhesive layer having embedded therein moderate reflectivity granular particles can be used in any building or wall construction, and can be placed under or around a foundation of a building or dwelling or on its below grade blind side retaining walls, etc.

Abstract in English: This invention relates to unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) charging system. The UAV charging system includes a primary UAV and an energy UAV with the primary UAV and the energy UAV having electric propulsion which is powered by a rechargeable battery. The energy UAV battery has a relatively greater capacity then the primary UAV battery and the energy UAV includes a charging element which connects to a battery charger on one end and has a charging connector at the other end. The primary UAV has a complementary connector for connecting to the charging connector. The system also includes a guidance controller which controls movement of the UAVs and which, when required, moves the UAVs to a charging position wherein the charging connector engages the complementary connector and the primary UAV battery is charged from the energy UAV battery through the charging system.

Abstract in English: This invention relates to a condensation measurement apparatus for measuring condensation of atmospheric airflow. The condensation measurement apparatus includes a plurality of condensation inducing elements which induces the formation of condensate on a relatively colder part of the element. Each element includes an enclosed condensate guiding portion which is in fluid contact with the colder part of the element and collects and guides condensate from the colder part of the element towards a nozzle. The nozzle is shaped and sized to induce formation and release of condensate droplets from the nozzle. The apparatus includes at least one image capturing device for capturing images of droplets released from the nozzles and an image processor associated with the device for processing and analysing the images to estimate the shape and size of droplets released by each nozzle and calculating the volume of condensate released from each nozzle.

Title in English: CONSCIOUSNESS LEVEL DETERMINATION METHOD AND COMPUTER PROGRAM
Abstract in English: A method for determining a consciousness level of a patient according to an embodiment of the present disclosure may include: a step of extracting components of one or more frequency bands from a first section of an EEG; a step of calculating a first index for each of the components of one or more frequency bands, wherein the first index is calculated based on a degree to which a magnitude of each of the components of one or more frequency bands with respect to a magnitude of a predetermined reference component in the first section exceeds a predetermined threshold value; a step of calculating a probability value for each of one or more patient statuses from the first index for each of the components of one or more frequency bands using a trained artificial neural network; and a step of determining the consciousness level of the patient based on the probability value for each of the one or more calculated patient statuses.

Title in English: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR THE SIMULTANEOUS PRODUCTION OF HYDROGEN BASED ENERGY AND CLEAN WATER FROM A SALINE OR CONTAMINATED WATER SOURCE
Abstract in English: A method for producing clean water from a contaminated water source, the method comprising the steps of: a) Locating a clean water generating device in fluid communication with the contaminated water source, the clean water generating device including a reaction chamber containing an ionic solution; b) Transferring contaminated water from the contaminated water source into the reaction chamber through an inlet in the clean water generating device; c) Generating an electrolysis reaction within the reaction chamber; d) Removing gas generated by the electrolysis reaction from the reaction chamber through an outlet therein; e) Combusting the gas generated by the electrolysis reaction; and f) Collecting clean water generated by the combustion of the gas.
